66/* Returns a hash code for P. */
67
68static hashval_t
69hash_name (const void *p)
70{
71 const struct lto_section_slot *ds = (const struct lto_section_slot *) p;
72 return (hashval_t) htab_hash_string (ds->name);
73}
74
75
76/* Returns nonzero if P1 and P2 are equal. */
77
78static int
79eq_name (const void *p1, const void *p2)
80{
81 const struct lto_section_slot *s1 =
82 (const struct lto_section_slot *) p1;
83 const struct lto_section_slot *s2 =
84 (const struct lto_section_slot *) p2;
85
86 return strcmp (s1->name, s2->name) == 0;
87}
88
89/* Free lto_section_slot */
90
91static void
92free_with_string (void *arg)
93{
94 struct lto_section_slot *s = (struct lto_section_slot *)arg;
95
96 free (CONST_CAST (char *, s->name));
97 free (arg);
98}

100/* Create section hash table */
101
102htab_t
103lto_obj_create_section_hash_table (void)
104{
105 return htab_create (37, hash_name, eq_name, free_with_string);
106}

108/* Delete an allocated integer KEY in the splay tree. */
109
110static void
111lto_splay_tree_delete_id (splay_tree_key key)
112{
113 free ((void *) key);
114}
115
116/* Compare splay tree node ids A and B. */
117
118static int
119lto_splay_tree_compare_ids (splay_tree_key a, splay_tree_key b)
120{
121 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT ai;
122 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT bi;
123
124 ai = *(unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *) a;
125 bi = *(unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *) b;
126
127 if (ai < bi)
128 return -1;
129 else if (ai > bi)
130 return 1;
131 return 0;
132}

134/* Look up splay tree node by ID in splay tree T. */
135
136static splay_tree_node
137lto_splay_tree_lookup (splay_tree t, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT id)
138{
139 return splay_tree_lookup (t, (splay_tree_key) &id);
140}

142/* Check if KEY has ID. */
143
144static bool
145lto_splay_tree_id_equal_p (splay_tree_key key, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT id)
146{
147 return *(unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *) key == id;
148}
149
150/* Insert a splay tree node into tree T with ID as key and FILE_DATA as value.
151 The ID is allocated separately because we need HOST_WIDE_INTs which may
152 be wider than a splay_tree_key. */
153
154static void
155lto_splay_tree_insert (splay_tree t, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT id,
156 struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data)
157{
158 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *idp = XCNEW (unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT);
159 *idp = id;
160 splay_tree_insert (t, (splay_tree_key) idp, (splay_tree_value) file_data);
161}

163/* Create a splay tree. */
164
165static splay_tree
166lto_splay_tree_new (void)
167{
168 return splay_tree_new (lto_splay_tree_compare_ids,
169 lto_splay_tree_delete_id,
170 NULL);
171}

173/* Return true when NODE has a clone that is analyzed (i.e. we need
174 to load its body even if the node itself is not needed). */
175
176static bool
177has_analyzed_clone_p (struct cgraph_node *node)
178{
179 struct cgraph_node *orig = node;
180 node = node->clones;
181 if (node)
182 while (node != orig)
183 {
184 if (node->analyzed)
185 return true;
186 if (node->clones)
187 node = node->clones;
188 else if (node->next_sibling_clone)
189 node = node->next_sibling_clone;
190 else
191 {
192 while (node != orig && !node->next_sibling_clone)
193 node = node->clone_of;
194 if (node != orig)
195 node = node->next_sibling_clone;
196 }
197 }
198 return false;
199}
200
201/* Read the function body for the function associated with NODE. */
202
203static void
204lto_materialize_function (struct cgraph_node *node)
205{
206 tree decl;
207
208 decl = node->decl;
209 /* Read in functions with body (analyzed nodes)
210 and also functions that are needed to produce virtual clones. */
211 if ((node->has_gimple_body_p () && node->analyzed)
212 || node->used_as_abstract_origin
213 || has_analyzed_clone_p (node))
214 {
215 /* Clones don't need to be read. */
216 if (node->clone_of)
217 return;
218 if (DECL_FUNCTION_PERSONALITY (decl) && !first_personality_decl)
219 first_personality_decl = DECL_FUNCTION_PERSONALITY (decl);
220 }
221
222 /* Let the middle end know about the function. */
223 rest_of_decl_compilation (decl, 1, 0);
224}

227/* Decode the content of memory pointed to by DATA in the in decl
228 state object STATE. DATA_IN points to a data_in structure for
229 decoding. Return the address after the decoded object in the
230 input. */
231
232static const uint32_t *
233lto_read_in_decl_state (struct data_in *data_in, const uint32_t *data,
234 struct lto_in_decl_state *state)
235{
236 uint32_t ix;
237 tree decl;
238 uint32_t i, j;
239
240 ix = *data++;
241 state->compressed = ix & 1;
242 ix /= 2;
243 decl = streamer_tree_cache_get_tree (data_in->reader_cache, ix);
244 if (!VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (decl))
245 {
246 gcc_assert (decl == void_type_node);
247 decl = NULL_TREE;
248 }
249 state->fn_decl = decl;
250
251 for (i = 0; i < LTO_N_DECL_STREAMS; i++)
252 {
253 uint32_t size = *data++;
254 vec<tree, va_gc> *decls = NULL;
255 vec_alloc (decls, size);
256
257 for (j = 0; j < size; j++)
258 vec_safe_push (decls,
259 streamer_tree_cache_get_tree (data_in->reader_cache,
260 data[j]));
261
262 state->streams[i] = decls;
263 data += size;
264 }
265
266 return data;
267}

270/* Global canonical type table. */
271static htab_t gimple_canonical_types;
272static hash_map<const_tree, hashval_t> *canonical_type_hash_cache;
273static unsigned long num_canonical_type_hash_entries;
274static unsigned long num_canonical_type_hash_queries;
275
276static void iterative_hash_canonical_type (tree type, inchash::hash &hstate);
277static hashval_t gimple_canonical_type_hash (const void *p);
278static void gimple_register_canonical_type_1 (tree t, hashval_t hash);
279
280/* Returning a hash value for gimple type TYPE.
281
282 The hash value returned is equal for types considered compatible
283 by gimple_canonical_types_compatible_p. */
284
285static hashval_t
286hash_canonical_type (tree type)
287{
288 inchash::hash hstate;
289 enum tree_code code;
290
291 /* We compute alias sets only for types that needs them.
292 Be sure we do not recurse to something else as we can not hash incomplete
293 types in a way they would have same hash value as compatible complete
294 types. */
295 gcc_checking_assert (type_with_alias_set_p (type));
296
297 /* Combine a few common features of types so that types are grouped into
298 smaller sets; when searching for existing matching types to merge,
299 only existing types having the same features as the new type will be
300 checked. */
301 code = tree_code_for_canonical_type_merging (TREE_CODE (type));
302 hstate.add_int (code);
303 hstate.add_int (TYPE_MODE (type));
304
305 /* Incorporate common features of numerical types. */
306 if (INTEGRAL_TYPE_P (type)
307 || SCALAR_FLOAT_TYPE_P (type)
308 || FIXED_POINT_TYPE_P (type)
309 || TREE_CODE (type) == OFFSET_TYPE
310 || POINTER_TYPE_P (type))
311 {
312 hstate.add_int (TYPE_PRECISION (type));
313 if (!type_with_interoperable_signedness (type))
314 hstate.add_int (TYPE_UNSIGNED (type));
315 }
316
317 if (VECTOR_TYPE_P (type))
318 {
319 hstate.add_int (TYPE_VECTOR_SUBPARTS (type));
320 hstate.add_int (TYPE_UNSIGNED (type));
321 }
322
323 if (TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE)
324 hstate.add_int (TYPE_UNSIGNED (type));
325
326 /* Fortran's C_SIGNED_CHAR is !TYPE_STRING_FLAG but needs to be
327 interoperable with "signed char". Unless all frontends are revisited to
328 agree on these types, we must ignore the flag completely. */
329
330 /* Fortran standard define C_PTR type that is compatible with every
331 C pointer. For this reason we need to glob all pointers into one.
332 Still pointers in different address spaces are not compatible. */
333 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (type))
334 hstate.add_int (TYPE_ADDR_SPACE (TREE_TYPE (type)));
335
336 /* For array types hash the domain bounds and the string flag. */
337 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE && TYPE_DOMAIN (type))
338 {
339 hstate.add_int (TYPE_STRING_FLAG (type));
340 /* OMP lowering can introduce error_mark_node in place of
341 random local decls in types. */
342 if (TYPE_MIN_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)) != error_mark_node)
343 inchash::add_expr (TYPE_MIN_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)), hstate);
344 if (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)) != error_mark_node)
345 inchash::add_expr (TYPE_MAX_VALUE (TYPE_DOMAIN (type)), hstate);
346 }
347
348 /* Recurse for aggregates with a single element type. */
349 if (TREE_CODE (type) == ARRAY_TYPE
350 || TREE_CODE (type) == COMPLEX_TYPE
351 || TREE_CODE (type) == VECTOR_TYPE)
352 iterative_hash_canonical_type (TREE_TYPE (type), hstate);
353
354 /* Incorporate function return and argument types. */
355 if (TREE_CODE (type) == FUNCTION_TYPE || TREE_CODE (type) == METHOD_TYPE)
356 {
357 unsigned na;
358 tree p;
359
360 iterative_hash_canonical_type (TREE_TYPE (type), hstate);
361
362 for (p = TYPE_ARG_TYPES (type), na = 0; p; p = TREE_CHAIN (p))
363 {
364 iterative_hash_canonical_type (TREE_VALUE (p), hstate);
365 na++;
366 }
367
368 hstate.add_int (na);
369 }
370
371 if (RECORD_OR_UNION_TYPE_P (type))
372 {
373 unsigned nf;
374 tree f;
375
376 for (f = TYPE_FIELDS (type), nf = 0; f; f = TREE_CHAIN (f))
377 if (TREE_CODE (f) == FIELD_DECL
378 && (! DECL_SIZE (f)
379 || ! integer_zerop (DECL_SIZE (f))))
380 {
381 iterative_hash_canonical_type (TREE_TYPE (f), hstate);
382 nf++;
383 }
384
385 hstate.add_int (nf);
386 }
387
388 return hstate.end();
389}
390
391/* Returning a hash value for gimple type TYPE combined with VAL. */
392
393static void
394iterative_hash_canonical_type (tree type, inchash::hash &hstate)
395{
396 hashval_t v;
397
398 /* All type variants have same TYPE_CANONICAL. */
399 type = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (type);
400
401 if (!canonical_type_used_p (type))
402 v = hash_canonical_type (type);
403 /* An already processed type. */
404 else if (TYPE_CANONICAL (type))
405 {
406 type = TYPE_CANONICAL (type);
407 v = gimple_canonical_type_hash (type);
408 }
409 else
410 {
411 /* Canonical types should not be able to form SCCs by design, this
412 recursion is just because we do not register canonical types in
413 optimal order. To avoid quadratic behavior also register the
414 type here. */
415 v = hash_canonical_type (type);
416 gimple_register_canonical_type_1 (type, v);
417 }
418 hstate.add_int (v);
419}
420
421/* Returns the hash for a canonical type P. */
422
423static hashval_t
424gimple_canonical_type_hash (const void *p)
425{
426 num_canonical_type_hash_queries++;
427 hashval_t *slot = canonical_type_hash_cache->get ((const_tree) p);
428 gcc_assert (slot != NULL);
429 return *slot;
430}

434/* Returns nonzero if P1 and P2 are equal. */
435
436static int
437gimple_canonical_type_eq (const void *p1, const void *p2)
438{
439 const_tree t1 = (const_tree) p1;
440 const_tree t2 = (const_tree) p2;
441 return gimple_canonical_types_compatible_p (CONST_CAST_TREE (t1),
442 CONST_CAST_TREE (t2));
443}
444
445/* Main worker for gimple_register_canonical_type. */
446
447static void
448gimple_register_canonical_type_1 (tree t, hashval_t hash)
449{
450 void **slot;
451
452 gcc_checking_assert (TYPE_P (t) && !TYPE_CANONICAL (t)
453 && type_with_alias_set_p (t)
454 && canonical_type_used_p (t));
455
456 slot = htab_find_slot_with_hash (gimple_canonical_types, t, hash, INSERT);
457 if (*slot)
458 {
459 tree new_type = (tree)(*slot);
460 gcc_checking_assert (new_type != t);
461 TYPE_CANONICAL (t) = new_type;
462 }
463 else
464 {
465 TYPE_CANONICAL (t) = t;
466 *slot = (void *) t;
467 /* Cache the just computed hash value. */
468 num_canonical_type_hash_entries++;
469 bool existed_p = canonical_type_hash_cache->put (t, hash);
470 gcc_assert (!existed_p);
471 }
472}
473
474/* Register type T in the global type table gimple_types and set
475 TYPE_CANONICAL of T accordingly.
476 This is used by LTO to merge structurally equivalent types for
477 type-based aliasing purposes across different TUs and languages.
478
479 ??? This merging does not exactly match how the tree.c middle-end
480 functions will assign TYPE_CANONICAL when new types are created
481 during optimization (which at least happens for pointer and array
482 types). */
483
484static void
485gimple_register_canonical_type (tree t)
486{
487 if (TYPE_CANONICAL (t) || !type_with_alias_set_p (t)
488 || !canonical_type_used_p (t))
489 return;
490
491 /* Canonical types are same among all complete variants. */
492 if (TYPE_CANONICAL (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t)))
493 TYPE_CANONICAL (t) = TYPE_CANONICAL (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t));
494 else
495 {
496 gimple_register_canonical_type_1 (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t),
497 hash_canonical_type (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t)));
498 TYPE_CANONICAL (t) = TYPE_CANONICAL (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t));
499 }
500}
501
502/* Re-compute TYPE_CANONICAL for NODE and related types. */
503
504static void
505lto_register_canonical_types (tree node, bool first_p)
506{
507 if (!node
508 || !TYPE_P (node))
509 return;
510
511 if (first_p)
512 TYPE_CANONICAL (node) = NULL_TREE;
513
514 if (POINTER_TYPE_P (node)
515 || TREE_CODE (node) == COMPLEX_TYPE
516 || TREE_CODE (node) == ARRAY_TYPE)
517 lto_register_canonical_types (TREE_TYPE (node), first_p);
518
519 if (!first_p)
520 gimple_register_canonical_type (node);
521}

524/* Remember trees that contains references to declarations. */
525static GTY(()) vec <tree, va_gc> *tree_with_vars;
526
527#define CHECK_VAR(tt) \
528 do \
529 { \
530 if ((tt) && VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (tt) \
531 && (TREE_PUBLIC (tt) || DECL_EXTERNAL (tt))) \
532 return true; \
533 } while (0)
534
535#define CHECK_NO_VAR(tt) \
536 gcc_checking_assert (!(tt) || !VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (tt))
537
538/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a tree_typed T. */
539
540static inline bool
541mentions_vars_p_typed (tree t)
542{
543 CHECK_NO_VAR (TREE_TYPE (t));
544 return false;
545}
546
547/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a tree_common T. */
548
549static inline bool
550mentions_vars_p_common (tree t)
551{
552 if (mentions_vars_p_typed (t))
553 return true;
554 CHECK_NO_VAR (TREE_CHAIN (t));
555 return false;
556}
557
558/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a decl_minimal T. */
559
560static inline bool
561mentions_vars_p_decl_minimal (tree t)
562{
563 if (mentions_vars_p_common (t))
564 return true;
565 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_NAME (t));
566 CHECK_VAR (DECL_CONTEXT (t));
567 return false;
568}
569
570/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a decl_common T. */
571
572static inline bool
573mentions_vars_p_decl_common (tree t)
574{
575 if (mentions_vars_p_decl_minimal (t))
576 return true;
577 CHECK_VAR (DECL_SIZE (t));
578 CHECK_VAR (DECL_SIZE_UNIT (t));
579 CHECK_VAR (DECL_INITIAL (t));
580 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_ATTRIBUTES (t));
581 CHECK_VAR (DECL_ABSTRACT_ORIGIN (t));
582 return false;
583}
584
585/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a decl_with_vis T. */
586
587static inline bool
588mentions_vars_p_decl_with_vis (tree t)
589{
590 if (mentions_vars_p_decl_common (t))
591 return true;
592
593 /* Accessor macro has side-effects, use field-name here. */
594 CHECK_NO_VAR (t->decl_with_vis.assembler_name);
595 return false;
596}
597
598/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a decl_non_common T. */
599
600static inline bool
601mentions_vars_p_decl_non_common (tree t)
602{
603 if (mentions_vars_p_decl_with_vis (t))
604 return true;
605 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_RESULT_FLD (t));
606 return false;
607}
608
609/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a decl_non_common T. */
610
611static bool
612mentions_vars_p_function (tree t)
613{
614 if (mentions_vars_p_decl_non_common (t))
615 return true;
616 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_ARGUMENTS (t));
617 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_VINDEX (t));
618 CHECK_VAR (DECL_FUNCTION_PERSONALITY (t));
619 return false;
620}
621
622/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a field_decl T. */
623
624static bool
625mentions_vars_p_field_decl (tree t)
626{
627 if (mentions_vars_p_decl_common (t))
628 return true;
629 CHECK_VAR (DECL_FIELD_OFFSET (t));
630 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_BIT_FIELD_TYPE (t));
631 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_QUALIFIER (t));
632 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_FIELD_BIT_OFFSET (t));
633 CHECK_NO_VAR (DECL_FCONTEXT (t));
634 return false;
635}
636
637/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a type T. */
638
639static bool
640mentions_vars_p_type (tree t)
641{
642 if (mentions_vars_p_common (t))
643 return true;
644 CHECK_NO_VAR (TYPE_CACHED_VALUES (t));
645 CHECK_VAR (TYPE_SIZE (t));
646 CHECK_VAR (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (t));
647 CHECK_NO_VAR (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (t));
648 CHECK_NO_VAR (TYPE_NAME (t));
649
650 CHECK_VAR (TYPE_MINVAL (t));
651 CHECK_VAR (TYPE_MAXVAL (t));
652
653 /* Accessor is for derived node types only. */
654 CHECK_NO_VAR (t->type_non_common.binfo);
655
656 CHECK_VAR (TYPE_CONTEXT (t));
657 CHECK_NO_VAR (TYPE_CANONICAL (t));
658 CHECK_NO_VAR (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t));
659 CHECK_NO_VAR (TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t));
660 return false;
661}
662
663/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a BINFO T. */
664
665static bool
666mentions_vars_p_binfo (tree t)
667{
668 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT i, n;
669
670 if (mentions_vars_p_common (t))
671 return true;
672 CHECK_VAR (BINFO_VTABLE (t));
673 CHECK_NO_VAR (BINFO_OFFSET (t));
674 CHECK_NO_VAR (BINFO_VIRTUALS (t));
675 CHECK_NO_VAR (BINFO_VPTR_FIELD (t));
676 n = vec_safe_length (BINFO_BASE_ACCESSES (t));
677 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
678 CHECK_NO_VAR (BINFO_BASE_ACCESS (t, i));
679 /* Do not walk BINFO_INHERITANCE_CHAIN, BINFO_SUBVTT_INDEX
680 and BINFO_VPTR_INDEX; these are used by C++ FE only. */
681 n = BINFO_N_BASE_BINFOS (t);
682 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
683 CHECK_NO_VAR (BINFO_BASE_BINFO (t, i));
684 return false;
685}
686
687/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of a CONSTRUCTOR T. */
688
689static bool
690mentions_vars_p_constructor (tree t)
691{
692 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT idx;
693 constructor_elt *ce;
694
695 if (mentions_vars_p_typed (t))
696 return true;
697
698 for (idx = 0; vec_safe_iterate (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (t), idx, &ce); idx++)
699 {
700 CHECK_NO_VAR (ce->index);
701 CHECK_VAR (ce->value);
702 }
703 return false;
704}
705
706/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of an expression tree T. */
707
708static bool
709mentions_vars_p_expr (tree t)
710{
711 int i;
712 if (mentions_vars_p_typed (t))
713 return true;
714 for (i = TREE_OPERAND_LENGTH (t) - 1; i >= 0; --i)
715 CHECK_VAR (TREE_OPERAND (t, i));
716 return false;
717}
718
719/* Check presence of pointers to decls in fields of an OMP_CLAUSE T. */
720
721static bool
722mentions_vars_p_omp_clause (tree t)
723{
724 int i;
725 if (mentions_vars_p_common (t))
726 return true;
727 for (i = omp_clause_num_ops[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (t)] - 1; i >= 0; --i)
728 CHECK_VAR (OMP_CLAUSE_OPERAND (t, i));
729 return false;
730}
731
732/* Check presence of pointers to decls that needs later fixup in T. */
733
734static bool
735mentions_vars_p (tree t)
736{
737 switch (TREE_CODE (t))
738 {
739 case IDENTIFIER_NODE:
740 break;
741
742 case TREE_LIST:
743 CHECK_VAR (TREE_VALUE (t));
744 CHECK_VAR (TREE_PURPOSE (t));
745 CHECK_NO_VAR (TREE_CHAIN (t));
746 break;
747
748 case FIELD_DECL:
749 return mentions_vars_p_field_decl (t);
750
751 case LABEL_DECL:
752 case CONST_DECL:
753 case PARM_DECL:
754 case RESULT_DECL:
755 case IMPORTED_DECL:
756 case NAMESPACE_DECL:
757 case NAMELIST_DECL:
758 return mentions_vars_p_decl_common (t);
759
760 case VAR_DECL:
761 return mentions_vars_p_decl_with_vis (t);
762
763 case TYPE_DECL:
764 return mentions_vars_p_decl_non_common (t);
765
766 case FUNCTION_DECL:
767 return mentions_vars_p_function (t);
768
769 case TREE_BINFO:
770 return mentions_vars_p_binfo (t);
771
772 case PLACEHOLDER_EXPR:
773 return mentions_vars_p_common (t);
774
775 case BLOCK:
776 case TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECL:
777 case OPTIMIZATION_NODE:
778 case TARGET_OPTION_NODE:
779 break;
780
781 case CONSTRUCTOR:
782 return mentions_vars_p_constructor (t);
783
784 case OMP_CLAUSE:
785 return mentions_vars_p_omp_clause (t);
786
787 default:
788 if (TYPE_P (t))
789 {
790 if (mentions_vars_p_type (t))
791 return true;
792 }
793 else if (EXPR_P (t))
794 {
795 if (mentions_vars_p_expr (t))
796 return true;
797 }
798 else if (CONSTANT_CLASS_P (t))
799 CHECK_NO_VAR (TREE_TYPE (t));
800 else
801 gcc_unreachable ();
802 }
803 return false;
804}
805
806
807/* Return the resolution for the decl with index INDEX from DATA_IN. */
808
809static enum ld_plugin_symbol_resolution
810get_resolution (struct data_in *data_in, unsigned index)
811{
812 if (data_in->globals_resolution.exists ())
813 {
814 ld_plugin_symbol_resolution_t ret;
815 /* We can have references to not emitted functions in
816 DECL_FUNCTION_PERSONALITY at least. So we can and have
817 to indeed return LDPR_UNKNOWN in some cases. */
818 if (data_in->globals_resolution.length () <= index)
819 return LDPR_UNKNOWN;
820 ret = data_in->globals_resolution[index];
821 return ret;
822 }
823 else
824 /* Delay resolution finding until decl merging. */
825 return LDPR_UNKNOWN;
826}
827
828/* We need to record resolutions until symbol table is read. */
829static void
830register_resolution (struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data, tree decl,
831 enum ld_plugin_symbol_resolution resolution)
832{
833 bool existed;
834 if (resolution == LDPR_UNKNOWN)
835 return;
836 if (!file_data->resolution_map)
837 file_data->resolution_map
838 = new hash_map<tree, ld_plugin_symbol_resolution>;
839 ld_plugin_symbol_resolution_t &res
840 = file_data->resolution_map->get_or_insert (decl, &existed);
841 if (!existed
842 || resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY
843 || resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF
844 || resolution == LDPR_PREVAILING_DEF_IRONLY_EXP)
845 res = resolution;
846}
847
848/* Register DECL with the global symbol table and change its
849 name if necessary to avoid name clashes for static globals across
850 different files. */
851
852static void
853lto_register_var_decl_in_symtab (struct data_in *data_in, tree decl,
854 unsigned ix)
855{
856 tree context;
857
858 /* Variable has file scope, not local. */
859 if (!TREE_PUBLIC (decl)
860 && !((context = decl_function_context (decl))
861 && auto_var_in_fn_p (decl, context)))
862 rest_of_decl_compilation (decl, 1, 0);
863
864 /* If this variable has already been declared, queue the
865 declaration for merging. */
866 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl))
867 register_resolution (data_in->file_data,
868 decl, get_resolution (data_in, ix));
869}
870
871
872/* Register DECL with the global symbol table and change its
873 name if necessary to avoid name clashes for static globals across
874 different files. DATA_IN contains descriptors and tables for the
875 file being read. */
876
877static void
878lto_register_function_decl_in_symtab (struct data_in *data_in, tree decl,
879 unsigned ix)
880{
881 /* If this variable has already been declared, queue the
882 declaration for merging. */
883 if (TREE_PUBLIC (decl) && !DECL_ABSTRACT_P (decl))
884 register_resolution (data_in->file_data,
885 decl, get_resolution (data_in, ix));
886}
887
888/* Check if T is a decl and needs register its resolution info. */
889
890static void
891lto_maybe_register_decl (struct data_in *data_in, tree t, unsigned ix)
892{
893 if (TREE_CODE (t) == VAR_DECL)
894 lto_register_var_decl_in_symtab (data_in, t, ix);
895 else if (TREE_CODE (t) == FUNCTION_DECL
896 && !DECL_BUILT_IN (t))
897 lto_register_function_decl_in_symtab (data_in, t, ix);
898}

901/* For the type T re-materialize it in the type variant list and
902 the pointer/reference-to chains. */
903
904static void
905lto_fixup_prevailing_type (tree t)
906{
907 /* The following re-creates proper variant lists while fixing up
908 the variant leaders. We do not stream TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT so the
909 variant list state before fixup is broken. */
910
911 /* If we are not our own variant leader link us into our new leaders
912 variant list. */
913 if (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t) != t)
914 {
915 tree mv = TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t);
916 TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (t) = TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (mv);
917 TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT (mv) = t;
918 }
919
920 /* The following reconstructs the pointer chains
921 of the new pointed-to type if we are a main variant. We do
922 not stream those so they are broken before fixup. */
923 if (TREE_CODE (t) == POINTER_TYPE
924 && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t) == t)
925 {
926 TYPE_NEXT_PTR_TO (t) = TYPE_POINTER_TO (TREE_TYPE (t));
927 TYPE_POINTER_TO (TREE_TYPE (t)) = t;
928 }
929 else if (TREE_CODE (t) == REFERENCE_TYPE
930 && TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t) == t)
931 {
932 TYPE_NEXT_REF_TO (t) = TYPE_REFERENCE_TO (TREE_TYPE (t));
933 TYPE_REFERENCE_TO (TREE_TYPE (t)) = t;
934 }
935}
936
937
938/* We keep prevailing tree SCCs in a hashtable with manual collision
939 handling (in case all hashes compare the same) and keep the colliding
940 entries in the tree_scc->next chain. */
941
942struct tree_scc
943{
944 tree_scc *next;
945 /* Hash of the whole SCC. */
946 hashval_t hash;
947 /* Number of trees in the SCC. */
948 unsigned len;
949 /* Number of possible entries into the SCC (tree nodes [0..entry_len-1]
950 which share the same individual tree hash). */
951 unsigned entry_len;
952 /* The members of the SCC.
953 We only need to remember the first entry node candidate for prevailing
954 SCCs (but of course have access to all entries for SCCs we are
955 processing).
956 ??? For prevailing SCCs we really only need hash and the first
957 entry candidate, but that's too awkward to implement. */
958 tree entries[1];
959};
960
961struct tree_scc_hasher : nofree_ptr_hash <tree_scc>
962{
963 static inline hashval_t hash (const tree_scc *);
964 static inline bool equal (const tree_scc *, const tree_scc *);
965};
966
967hashval_t
968tree_scc_hasher::hash (const tree_scc *scc)
969{
970 return scc->hash;
971}
972
973bool
974tree_scc_hasher::equal (const tree_scc *scc1, const tree_scc *scc2)
975{
976 if (scc1->hash != scc2->hash
977 || scc1->len != scc2->len
978 || scc1->entry_len != scc2->entry_len)
979 return false;
980 return true;
981}
982
983static hash_table<tree_scc_hasher> *tree_scc_hash;
984static struct obstack tree_scc_hash_obstack;
985
986static unsigned long num_merged_types;
987static unsigned long num_prevailing_types;
988static unsigned long num_type_scc_trees;
989static unsigned long total_scc_size;
990static unsigned long num_sccs_read;
991static unsigned long total_scc_size_merged;
992static unsigned long num_sccs_merged;
993static unsigned long num_scc_compares;
994static unsigned long num_scc_compare_collisions;
995
996
997/* Compare the two entries T1 and T2 of two SCCs that are possibly equal,
998 recursing through in-SCC tree edges. Returns true if the SCCs entered
999 through T1 and T2 are equal and fills in *MAP with the pairs of
1000 SCC entries we visited, starting with (*MAP)[0] = T1 and (*MAP)[1] = T2. */
1001
1002static bool
1003compare_tree_sccs_1 (tree t1, tree t2, tree **map)
1004{
1005 enum tree_code code;
1006
1007 /* Mark already visited nodes. */
1008 TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (t2) = 1;
1009
1010 /* Push the pair onto map. */
1011 (*map)[0] = t1;
1012 (*map)[1] = t2;
1013 *map = *map + 2;
1014
1015 /* Compare value-fields. */
1016#define compare_values(X) \
1017 do { \
1018 if (X(t1) != X(t2)) \
1019 return false; \
1020 } while (0)
1021
1022 compare_values (TREE_CODE);
1023 code = TREE_CODE (t1);
1024
1025 if (!TYPE_P (t1))
1026 {
1027 compare_values (TREE_SIDE_EFFECTS);
1028 compare_values (TREE_CONSTANT);
1029 compare_values (TREE_READONLY);
1030 compare_values (TREE_PUBLIC);
1031 }
1032 compare_values (TREE_ADDRESSABLE);
1033 compare_values (TREE_THIS_VOLATILE);
1034 if (DECL_P (t1))
1035 compare_values (DECL_UNSIGNED);
1036 else if (TYPE_P (t1))
1037 compare_values (TYPE_UNSIGNED);
1038 if (TYPE_P (t1))
1039 compare_values (TYPE_ARTIFICIAL);
1040 else
1041 compare_values (TREE_NO_WARNING);
1042 compare_values (TREE_NOTHROW);
1043 compare_values (TREE_STATIC);
1044 if (code != TREE_BINFO)
1045 compare_values (TREE_PRIVATE);
1046 compare_values (TREE_PROTECTED);
1047 compare_values (TREE_DEPRECATED);
1048 if (TYPE_P (t1))
1049 {
1050 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (t1))
1051 compare_values (TYPE_REVERSE_STORAGE_ORDER);
1052 else
1053 compare_values (TYPE_SATURATING);
1054 compare_values (TYPE_ADDR_SPACE);
1055 }
1056 else if (code == SSA_NAME)
1057 compare_values (SSA_NAME_IS_DEFAULT_DEF);
1058
1059 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_INT_CST))
1060 {
1061 if (!wi::eq_p (t1, t2))
1062 return false;
1063 }
1064
1065 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_REAL_CST))
1066 {
1067 /* ??? No suitable compare routine available. */
1068 REAL_VALUE_TYPE r1 = TREE_REAL_CST (t1);
1069 REAL_VALUE_TYPE r2 = TREE_REAL_CST (t2);
1070 if (r1.cl != r2.cl
1071 || r1.decimal != r2.decimal
1072 || r1.sign != r2.sign
1073 || r1.signalling != r2.signalling
1074 || r1.canonical != r2.canonical
1075 || r1.uexp != r2.uexp)
1076 return false;
1077 for (unsigned i = 0; i < SIGSZ; ++i)
1078 if (r1.sig[i] != r2.sig[i])
1079 return false;
1080 }
1081
1082 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_FIXED_CST))
1083 if (!fixed_compare (EQ_EXPR,
1084 TREE_FIXED_CST_PTR (t1), TREE_FIXED_CST_PTR (t2)))
1085 return false;
1086
1087 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_COMMON))
1088 {
1089 compare_values (DECL_MODE);
1090 compare_values (DECL_NONLOCAL);
1091 compare_values (DECL_VIRTUAL_P);
1092 compare_values (DECL_IGNORED_P);
1093 compare_values (DECL_ABSTRACT_P);
1094 compare_values (DECL_ARTIFICIAL);
1095 compare_values (DECL_USER_ALIGN);
1096 compare_values (DECL_PRESERVE_P);
1097 compare_values (DECL_EXTERNAL);
1098 compare_values (DECL_GIMPLE_REG_P);
1099 compare_values (DECL_ALIGN);
1100 if (code == LABEL_DECL)
1101 {
1102 compare_values (EH_LANDING_PAD_NR);
1103 compare_values (LABEL_DECL_UID);
1104 }
1105 else if (code == FIELD_DECL)
1106 {
1107 compare_values (DECL_PACKED);
1108 compare_values (DECL_NONADDRESSABLE_P);
1109 compare_values (DECL_OFFSET_ALIGN);
1110 }
1111 else if (code == VAR_DECL)
1112 {
1113 compare_values (DECL_HAS_DEBUG_EXPR_P);
1114 compare_values (DECL_NONLOCAL_FRAME);
1115 }
1116 if (code == RESULT_DECL
1117 || code == PARM_DECL
1118 || code == VAR_DECL)
1119 {
1120 compare_values (DECL_BY_REFERENCE);
1121 if (code == VAR_DECL
1122 || code == PARM_DECL)
1123 compare_values (DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P);
1124 }
1125 }
1126
1127 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_WRTL))
1128 compare_values (DECL_REGISTER);
1129
1130 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_WITH_VIS))
1131 {
1132 compare_values (DECL_COMMON);
1133 compare_values (DECL_DLLIMPORT_P);
1134 compare_values (DECL_WEAK);
1135 compare_values (DECL_SEEN_IN_BIND_EXPR_P);
1136 compare_values (DECL_COMDAT);
1137 compare_values (DECL_VISIBILITY);
1138 compare_values (DECL_VISIBILITY_SPECIFIED);
1139 if (code == VAR_DECL)
1140 {
1141 compare_values (DECL_HARD_REGISTER);
1142 /* DECL_IN_TEXT_SECTION is set during final asm output only. */
1143 compare_values (DECL_IN_CONSTANT_POOL);
1144 }
1145 }
1146
1147 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_FUNCTION_DECL))
1148 {
1149 compare_values (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS);
1150 compare_values (DECL_STATIC_CONSTRUCTOR);
1151 compare_values (DECL_STATIC_DESTRUCTOR);
1152 compare_values (DECL_UNINLINABLE);
1153 compare_values (DECL_POSSIBLY_INLINED);
1154 compare_values (DECL_IS_NOVOPS);
1155 compare_values (DECL_IS_RETURNS_TWICE);
1156 compare_values (DECL_IS_MALLOC);
1157 compare_values (DECL_IS_OPERATOR_NEW);
1158 compare_values (DECL_DECLARED_INLINE_P);
1159 compare_values (DECL_STATIC_CHAIN);
1160 compare_values (DECL_NO_INLINE_WARNING_P);
1161 compare_values (DECL_NO_INSTRUMENT_FUNCTION_ENTRY_EXIT);
1162 compare_values (DECL_NO_LIMIT_STACK);
1163 compare_values (DECL_DISREGARD_INLINE_LIMITS);
1164 compare_values (DECL_PURE_P);
1165 compare_values (DECL_LOOPING_CONST_OR_PURE_P);
1166 compare_values (DECL_FINAL_P);
1167 compare_values (DECL_CXX_CONSTRUCTOR_P);
1168 compare_values (DECL_CXX_DESTRUCTOR_P);
1169 if (DECL_BUILT_IN_CLASS (t1) != NOT_BUILT_IN)
1170 compare_values (DECL_FUNCTION_CODE);
1171 }
1172
1173 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_TYPE_COMMON))
1174 {
1175 compare_values (TYPE_MODE);
1176 compare_values (TYPE_STRING_FLAG);
1177 compare_values (TYPE_NEEDS_CONSTRUCTING);
1178 if (RECORD_OR_UNION_TYPE_P (t1))
1179 {
1180 compare_values (TYPE_TRANSPARENT_AGGR);
1181 compare_values (TYPE_FINAL_P);
1182 }
1183 else if (code == ARRAY_TYPE)
1184 compare_values (TYPE_NONALIASED_COMPONENT);
1185 if (AGGREGATE_TYPE_P (t1))
1186 compare_values (TYPE_TYPELESS_STORAGE);
1187 compare_values (TYPE_PACKED);
1188 compare_values (TYPE_RESTRICT);
1189 compare_values (TYPE_USER_ALIGN);
1190 compare_values (TYPE_READONLY);
1191 compare_values (TYPE_PRECISION);
1192 compare_values (TYPE_ALIGN);
1193 /* Do not compare TYPE_ALIAS_SET. Doing so introduce ordering issues
1194 with calls to get_alias_set which may initialize it for streamed
1195 in types. */
1196 }
1197
1198 /* We don't want to compare locations, so there is nothing do compare
1199 for TS_EXP. */
1200
1201 /* BLOCKs are function local and we don't merge anything there, so
1202 simply refuse to merge. */
1203 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_BLOCK))
1204 return false;
1205
1206 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECL))
1207 if (strcmp (TRANSLATION_UNIT_LANGUAGE (t1),
1208 TRANSLATION_UNIT_LANGUAGE (t2)) != 0)
1209 return false;
1210
1211 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_TARGET_OPTION))
1212 if (!cl_target_option_eq (TREE_TARGET_OPTION (t1), TREE_TARGET_OPTION (t2)))
1213 return false;
1214
1215 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_OPTIMIZATION))
1216 if (memcmp (TREE_OPTIMIZATION (t1), TREE_OPTIMIZATION (t2),
1217 sizeof (struct cl_optimization)) != 0)
1218 return false;
1219
1220 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_BINFO))
1221 if (vec_safe_length (BINFO_BASE_ACCESSES (t1))
1222 != vec_safe_length (BINFO_BASE_ACCESSES (t2)))
1223 return false;
1224
1225 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_CONSTRUCTOR))
1226 compare_values (CONSTRUCTOR_NELTS);
1227
1228 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_IDENTIFIER))
1229 if (IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (t1) != IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (t2)
1230 || memcmp (IDENTIFIER_POINTER (t1), IDENTIFIER_POINTER (t2),
1231 IDENTIFIER_LENGTH (t1)) != 0)
1232 return false;
1233
1234 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_STRING))
1235 if (TREE_STRING_LENGTH (t1) != TREE_STRING_LENGTH (t2)
1236 || memcmp (TREE_STRING_POINTER (t1), TREE_STRING_POINTER (t2),
1237 TREE_STRING_LENGTH (t1)) != 0)
1238 return false;
1239
1240 if (code == OMP_CLAUSE)
1241 {
1242 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE);
1243 switch (OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (t1))
1244 {
1245 case OMP_CLAUSE_DEFAULT:
1246 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_DEFAULT_KIND);
1247 break;
1248 case OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE:
1249 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_SCHEDULE_KIND);
1250 break;
1251 case OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND:
1252 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_DEPEND_KIND);
1253 break;
1254 case OMP_CLAUSE_MAP:
1255 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_MAP_KIND);
1256 break;
1257 case OMP_CLAUSE_PROC_BIND:
1258 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_PROC_BIND_KIND);
1259 break;
1260 case OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION:
1261 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_CODE);
1262 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_GIMPLE_INIT);
1263 compare_values (OMP_CLAUSE_REDUCTION_GIMPLE_MERGE);
1264 break;
1265 default:
1266 break;
1267 }
1268 }
1269
1270#undef compare_values
1271
1272
1273 /* Compare pointer fields. */
1274
1275 /* Recurse. Search & Replaced from DFS_write_tree_body.
1276 Folding the early checks into the compare_tree_edges recursion
1277 macro makes debugging way quicker as you are able to break on
1278 compare_tree_sccs_1 and simply finish until a call returns false
1279 to spot the SCC members with the difference. */
1280#define compare_tree_edges(E1, E2) \
1281 do { \
1282 tree t1_ = (E1), t2_ = (E2); \
1283 if (t1_ != t2_ \
1284 && (!t1_ || !t2_ \
1285 || !TREE_VISITED (t2_) \
1286 || (!TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (t2_) \
1287 && !compare_tree_sccs_1 (t1_, t2_, map)))) \
1288 return false; \
1289 /* Only non-NULL trees outside of the SCC may compare equal. */ \
1290 gcc_checking_assert (t1_ != t2_ || (!t2_ || !TREE_VISITED (t2_))); \
1291 } while (0)
1292
1293 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_TYPED))
1294 {
1295 if (code != IDENTIFIER_NODE)
1296 compare_tree_edges (TREE_TYPE (t1), TREE_TYPE (t2));
1297 }
1298
1299 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_VECTOR))
1300 {
1301 unsigned i;
1302 /* Note that the number of elements for EXPR has already been emitted
1303 in EXPR's header (see streamer_write_tree_header). */
1304 for (i = 0; i < VECTOR_CST_NELTS (t1); ++i)
1305 compare_tree_edges (VECTOR_CST_ELT (t1, i), VECTOR_CST_ELT (t2, i));
1306 }
1307
1308 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_COMPLEX))
1309 {
1310 compare_tree_edges (TREE_REALPART (t1), TREE_REALPART (t2));
1311 compare_tree_edges (TREE_IMAGPART (t1), TREE_IMAGPART (t2));
1312 }
1313
1314 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_MINIMAL))
1315 {
1316 compare_tree_edges (DECL_NAME (t1), DECL_NAME (t2));
1317 /* ??? Global decls from different TUs have non-matching
1318 TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECLs. Only consider a small set of
1319 decls equivalent, we should not end up merging others. */
1320 if ((code == TYPE_DECL
1321 || code == NAMESPACE_DECL
1322 || code == IMPORTED_DECL
1323 || code == CONST_DECL
1324 || (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (t1)
1325 && (TREE_PUBLIC (t1) || DECL_EXTERNAL (t1))))
1326 && DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (t1) && DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (t2))
1327 ;
1328 else
1329 compare_tree_edges (DECL_CONTEXT (t1), DECL_CONTEXT (t2));
1330 }
1331
1332 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_COMMON))
1333 {
1334 compare_tree_edges (DECL_SIZE (t1), DECL_SIZE (t2));
1335 compare_tree_edges (DECL_SIZE_UNIT (t1), DECL_SIZE_UNIT (t2));
1336 compare_tree_edges (DECL_ATTRIBUTES (t1), DECL_ATTRIBUTES (t2));
1337 compare_tree_edges (DECL_ABSTRACT_ORIGIN (t1), DECL_ABSTRACT_ORIGIN (t2));
1338 if ((code == VAR_DECL
1339 || code == PARM_DECL)
1340 && DECL_HAS_VALUE_EXPR_P (t1))
1341 compare_tree_edges (DECL_VALUE_EXPR (t1), DECL_VALUE_EXPR (t2));
1342 if (code == VAR_DECL
1343 && DECL_HAS_DEBUG_EXPR_P (t1))
1344 compare_tree_edges (DECL_DEBUG_EXPR (t1), DECL_DEBUG_EXPR (t2));
1345 /* LTO specific edges. */
1346 if (code != FUNCTION_DECL
1347 && code != TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECL)
1348 compare_tree_edges (DECL_INITIAL (t1), DECL_INITIAL (t2));
1349 }
1350
1351 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_NON_COMMON))
1352 {
1353 if (code == FUNCTION_DECL)
1354 {
1355 tree a1, a2;
1356 for (a1 = DECL_ARGUMENTS (t1), a2 = DECL_ARGUMENTS (t2);
1357 a1 || a2;
1358 a1 = TREE_CHAIN (a1), a2 = TREE_CHAIN (a2))
1359 compare_tree_edges (a1, a2);
1360 compare_tree_edges (DECL_RESULT (t1), DECL_RESULT (t2));
1361 }
1362 else if (code == TYPE_DECL)
1363 compare_tree_edges (DECL_ORIGINAL_TYPE (t1), DECL_ORIGINAL_TYPE (t2));
1364 }
1365
1366 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_DECL_WITH_VIS))
1367 {
1368 /* Make sure we don't inadvertently set the assembler name. */
1369 if (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME_SET_P (t1))
1370 compare_tree_edges (DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (t1),
1371 DECL_ASSEMBLER_NAME (t2));
1372 }
1373
1374 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_FIELD_DECL))
1375 {
1376 compare_tree_edges (DECL_FIELD_OFFSET (t1), DECL_FIELD_OFFSET (t2));
1377 compare_tree_edges (DECL_BIT_FIELD_TYPE (t1), DECL_BIT_FIELD_TYPE (t2));
1378 compare_tree_edges (DECL_BIT_FIELD_REPRESENTATIVE (t1),
1379 DECL_BIT_FIELD_REPRESENTATIVE (t2));
1380 compare_tree_edges (DECL_FIELD_BIT_OFFSET (t1),
1381 DECL_FIELD_BIT_OFFSET (t2));
1382 compare_tree_edges (DECL_FCONTEXT (t1), DECL_FCONTEXT (t2));
1383 }
1384
1385 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_FUNCTION_DECL))
1386 {
1387 compare_tree_edges (DECL_FUNCTION_PERSONALITY (t1),
1388 DECL_FUNCTION_PERSONALITY (t2));
1389 compare_tree_edges (DECL_VINDEX (t1), DECL_VINDEX (t2));
1390 compare_tree_edges (DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_TARGET (t1),
1391 DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_TARGET (t2));
1392 compare_tree_edges (DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_OPTIMIZATION (t1),
1393 DECL_FUNCTION_SPECIFIC_OPTIMIZATION (t2));
1394 }
1395
1396 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_TYPE_COMMON))
1397 {
1398 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_SIZE (t1), TYPE_SIZE (t2));
1399 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (t1), TYPE_SIZE_UNIT (t2));
1400 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (t1), TYPE_ATTRIBUTES (t2));
1401 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_NAME (t1), TYPE_NAME (t2));
1402 /* Do not compare TYPE_POINTER_TO or TYPE_REFERENCE_TO. They will be
1403 reconstructed during fixup. */
1404 /* Do not compare TYPE_NEXT_VARIANT, we reconstruct the variant lists
1405 during fixup. */
1406 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t1), TYPE_MAIN_VARIANT (t2));
1407 /* ??? Global types from different TUs have non-matching
1408 TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECLs. Still merge them if they are otherwise
1409 equal. */
1410 if (TYPE_FILE_SCOPE_P (t1) && TYPE_FILE_SCOPE_P (t2))
1411 ;
1412 else
1413 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_CONTEXT (t1), TYPE_CONTEXT (t2));
1414 /* TYPE_CANONICAL is re-computed during type merging, so do not
1415 compare it here. */
1416 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_STUB_DECL (t1), TYPE_STUB_DECL (t2));
1417 }
1418
1419 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_TYPE_NON_COMMON))
1420 {
1421 if (code == ENUMERAL_TYPE)
1422 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_VALUES (t1), TYPE_VALUES (t2));
1423 else if (code == ARRAY_TYPE)
1424 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_DOMAIN (t1), TYPE_DOMAIN (t2));
1425 else if (RECORD_OR_UNION_TYPE_P (t1))
1426 {
1427 tree f1, f2;
1428 for (f1 = TYPE_FIELDS (t1), f2 = TYPE_FIELDS (t2);
1429 f1 || f2;
1430 f1 = TREE_CHAIN (f1), f2 = TREE_CHAIN (f2))
1431 compare_tree_edges (f1, f2);
1432 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_BINFO (t1), TYPE_BINFO (t2));
1433 }
1434 else if (code == FUNCTION_TYPE
1435 || code == METHOD_TYPE)
1436 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_ARG_TYPES (t1), TYPE_ARG_TYPES (t2));
1437 if (!POINTER_TYPE_P (t1))
1438 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_MINVAL (t1), TYPE_MINVAL (t2));
1439 compare_tree_edges (TYPE_MAXVAL (t1), TYPE_MAXVAL (t2));
1440 }
1441
1442 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_LIST))
1443 {
1444 compare_tree_edges (TREE_PURPOSE (t1), TREE_PURPOSE (t2));
1445 compare_tree_edges (TREE_VALUE (t1), TREE_VALUE (t2));
1446 compare_tree_edges (TREE_CHAIN (t1), TREE_CHAIN (t2));
1447 }
1448
1449 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_VEC))
1450 for (int i = 0; i < TREE_VEC_LENGTH (t1); i++)
1451 compare_tree_edges (TREE_VEC_ELT (t1, i), TREE_VEC_ELT (t2, i));
1452
1453 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_EXP))
1454 {
1455 for (int i = 0; i < TREE_OPERAND_LENGTH (t1); i++)
1456 compare_tree_edges (TREE_OPERAND (t1, i),
1457 TREE_OPERAND (t2, i));
1458
1459 /* BLOCKs are function local and we don't merge anything there. */
1460 if (TREE_BLOCK (t1) || TREE_BLOCK (t2))
1461 return false;
1462 }
1463
1464 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_BINFO))
1465 {
1466 unsigned i;
1467 tree t;
1468 /* Lengths have already been compared above. */
1469 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (*BINFO_BASE_BINFOS (t1), i, t)
1470 compare_tree_edges (t, BINFO_BASE_BINFO (t2, i));
1471 FOR_EACH_VEC_SAFE_ELT (BINFO_BASE_ACCESSES (t1), i, t)
1472 compare_tree_edges (t, BINFO_BASE_ACCESS (t2, i));
1473 compare_tree_edges (BINFO_OFFSET (t1), BINFO_OFFSET (t2));
1474 compare_tree_edges (BINFO_VTABLE (t1), BINFO_VTABLE (t2));
1475 compare_tree_edges (BINFO_VPTR_FIELD (t1), BINFO_VPTR_FIELD (t2));
1476 /* Do not walk BINFO_INHERITANCE_CHAIN, BINFO_SUBVTT_INDEX
1477 and BINFO_VPTR_INDEX; these are used by C++ FE only. */
1478 }
1479
1480 if (CODE_CONTAINS_STRUCT (code, TS_CONSTRUCTOR))
1481 {
1482 unsigned i;
1483 tree index, value;
1484 /* Lengths have already been compared above. */
1485 FOR_EACH_CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (CONSTRUCTOR_ELTS (t1), i, index, value)
1486 {
1487 compare_tree_edges (index, CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (t2, i)->index);
1488 compare_tree_edges (value, CONSTRUCTOR_ELT (t2, i)->value);
1489 }
1490 }
1491
1492 if (code == OMP_CLAUSE)
1493 {
1494 int i;
1495
1496 for (i = 0; i < omp_clause_num_ops[OMP_CLAUSE_CODE (t1)]; i++)
1497 compare_tree_edges (OMP_CLAUSE_OPERAND (t1, i),
1498 OMP_CLAUSE_OPERAND (t2, i));
1499 compare_tree_edges (OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (t1), OMP_CLAUSE_CHAIN (t2));
1500 }
1501
1502#undef compare_tree_edges
1503
1504 return true;
1505}
1506
1507/* Compare the tree scc SCC to the prevailing candidate PSCC, filling
1508 out MAP if they are equal. */
1509
1510static bool
1511compare_tree_sccs (tree_scc *pscc, tree_scc *scc,
1512 tree *map)
1513{
1514 /* Assume SCC entry hashes are sorted after their cardinality. Which
1515 means we can simply take the first n-tuple of equal hashes
1516 (which is recorded as entry_len) and do n SCC entry candidate
1517 comparisons. */
1518 for (unsigned i = 0; i < pscc->entry_len; ++i)
1519 {
1520 tree *mapp = map;
1521 num_scc_compare_collisions++;
1522 if (compare_tree_sccs_1 (pscc->entries[0], scc->entries[i], &mapp))
1523 {
1524 /* Equal - no need to reset TREE_VISITED or TREE_ASM_WRITTEN
1525 on the scc as all trees will be freed. */
1526 return true;
1527 }
1528 /* Reset TREE_ASM_WRITTEN on scc for the next compare or in case
1529 the SCC prevails. */
1530 for (unsigned j = 0; j < scc->len; ++j)
1531 TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (scc->entries[j]) = 0;
1532 }
1533
1534 return false;
1535}
1536
1537/* QSort sort function to sort a map of two pointers after the 2nd
1538 pointer. */
1539
1540static int
1541cmp_tree (const void *p1_, const void *p2_)
1542{
1543 tree *p1 = (tree *)(const_cast<void *>(p1_));
1544 tree *p2 = (tree *)(const_cast<void *>(p2_));
1545 if (p1[1] == p2[1])
1546 return 0;
1547 return ((uintptr_t)p1[1] < (uintptr_t)p2[1]) ? -1 : 1;
1548}
1549
1550/* Try to unify the SCC with nodes FROM to FROM + LEN in CACHE and
1551 hash value SCC_HASH with an already recorded SCC. Return true if
1552 that was successful, otherwise return false. */
1553
1554static bool
1555unify_scc (struct data_in *data_in, unsigned from,
1556 unsigned len, unsigned scc_entry_len, hashval_t scc_hash)
1557{
1558 bool unified_p = false;
1559 struct streamer_tree_cache_d *cache = data_in->reader_cache;
1560 tree_scc *scc
1561 = (tree_scc *) alloca (sizeof (tree_scc) + (len - 1) * sizeof (tree));
1562 scc->next = NULL;
1563 scc->hash = scc_hash;
1564 scc->len = len;
1565 scc->entry_len = scc_entry_len;
1566 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; ++i)
1567 {
1568 tree t = streamer_tree_cache_get_tree (cache, from + i);
1569 scc->entries[i] = t;
1570 /* Do not merge SCCs with local entities inside them. Also do
1571 not merge TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECLs. */
1572 if (TREE_CODE (t) == TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECL
1573 || (VAR_OR_FUNCTION_DECL_P (t)
1574 && !(TREE_PUBLIC (t) || DECL_EXTERNAL (t)))
1575 || TREE_CODE (t) == LABEL_DECL)
1576 {
1577 /* Avoid doing any work for these cases and do not worry to
1578 record the SCCs for further merging. */
1579 return false;
1580 }
1581 }
1582
1583 /* Look for the list of candidate SCCs to compare against. */
1584 tree_scc **slot;
1585 slot = tree_scc_hash->find_slot_with_hash (scc, scc_hash, INSERT);
1586 if (*slot)
1587 {
1588 /* Try unifying against each candidate. */
1589 num_scc_compares++;
1590
1591 /* Set TREE_VISITED on the scc so we can easily identify tree nodes
1592 outside of the scc when following tree edges. Make sure
1593 that TREE_ASM_WRITTEN is unset so we can use it as 2nd bit
1594 to track whether we visited the SCC member during the compare.
1595 We cannot use TREE_VISITED on the pscc members as the extended
1596 scc and pscc can overlap. */
1597 for (unsigned i = 0; i < scc->len; ++i)
1598 {
1599 TREE_VISITED (scc->entries[i]) = 1;
1600 gcc_checking_assert (!TREE_ASM_WRITTEN (scc->entries[i]));
1601 }
1602
1603 tree *map = XALLOCAVEC (tree, 2 * len);
1604 for (tree_scc *pscc = *slot; pscc; pscc = pscc->next)
1605 {
1606 if (!compare_tree_sccs (pscc, scc, map))
1607 continue;
1608
1609 /* Found an equal SCC. */
1610 unified_p = true;
1611 num_scc_compare_collisions--;
1612 num_sccs_merged++;
1613 total_scc_size_merged += len;
1614
1615 if (flag_checking)
1616 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; ++i)
1617 {
1618 tree t = map[2*i+1];
1619 enum tree_code code = TREE_CODE (t);
1620 /* IDENTIFIER_NODEs should be singletons and are merged by the
1621 streamer. The others should be singletons, too, and we
1622 should not merge them in any way. */
1623 gcc_assert (code != TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECL
1624 && code != IDENTIFIER_NODE);
1625 }
1626
1627 /* Fixup the streamer cache with the prevailing nodes according
1628 to the tree node mapping computed by compare_tree_sccs. */
1629 if (len == 1)
1630 {
1631 lto_maybe_register_decl (data_in, pscc->entries[0], from);
1632 streamer_tree_cache_replace_tree (cache, pscc->entries[0], from);
1633 }
1634 else
1635 {
1636 tree *map2 = XALLOCAVEC (tree, 2 * len);
1637 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; ++i)
1638 {
1639 map2[i*2] = (tree)(uintptr_t)(from + i);
1640 map2[i*2+1] = scc->entries[i];
1641 }
1642 qsort (map2, len, 2 * sizeof (tree), cmp_tree);
1643 qsort (map, len, 2 * sizeof (tree), cmp_tree);
1644 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; ++i)
1645 {
1646 lto_maybe_register_decl (data_in, map[2*i],
1647 (uintptr_t)map2[2*i]);
1648 streamer_tree_cache_replace_tree (cache, map[2*i],
1649 (uintptr_t)map2[2*i]);
1650 }
1651 }
1652
1653 /* Free the tree nodes from the read SCC. */
1654 data_in->location_cache.revert_location_cache ();
1655 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; ++i)
1656 {
1657 if (TYPE_P (scc->entries[i]))
1658 num_merged_types++;
1659 free_node (scc->entries[i]);
1660 }
1661
1662 break;
1663 }
1664
1665 /* Reset TREE_VISITED if we didn't unify the SCC with another. */
1666 if (!unified_p)
1667 for (unsigned i = 0; i < scc->len; ++i)
1668 TREE_VISITED (scc->entries[i]) = 0;
1669 }
1670
1671 /* If we didn't unify it to any candidate duplicate the relevant
1672 pieces to permanent storage and link it into the chain. */
1673 if (!unified_p)
1674 {
1675 tree_scc *pscc
1676 = XOBNEWVAR (&tree_scc_hash_obstack, tree_scc, sizeof (tree_scc));
1677 memcpy (pscc, scc, sizeof (tree_scc));
1678 pscc->next = (*slot);
1679 *slot = pscc;
1680 }
1681 return unified_p;
1682}
1683
1684
1685/* Read all the symbols from buffer DATA, using descriptors in DECL_DATA.
1686 RESOLUTIONS is the set of symbols picked by the linker (read from the
1687 resolution file when the linker plugin is being used). */
1688
1689static void
1690lto_read_decls (struct lto_file_decl_data *decl_data, const void *data,
1691 vec<ld_plugin_symbol_resolution_t> resolutions)
1692{
1693 const struct lto_decl_header *header = (const struct lto_decl_header *) data;
1694 const int decl_offset = sizeof (struct lto_decl_header);
1695 const int main_offset = decl_offset + header->decl_state_size;
1696 const int string_offset = main_offset + header->main_size;
1697 struct data_in *data_in;
1698 unsigned int i;
1699 const uint32_t *data_ptr, *data_end;
1700 uint32_t num_decl_states;
1701
1702 lto_input_block ib_main ((const char *) data + main_offset,
1703 header->main_size, decl_data->mode_table);
1704
1705 data_in = lto_data_in_create (decl_data, (const char *) data + string_offset,
1706 header->string_size, resolutions);
1707
1708 /* We do not uniquify the pre-loaded cache entries, those are middle-end
1709 internal types that should not be merged. */
1710
1711 /* Read the global declarations and types. */
1712 while (ib_main.p < ib_main.len)
1713 {
1714 tree t;
1715 unsigned from = data_in->reader_cache->nodes.length ();
1716 /* Read and uniquify SCCs as in the input stream. */
1717 enum LTO_tags tag = streamer_read_record_start (&ib_main);
1718 if (tag == LTO_tree_scc)
1719 {
1720 unsigned len_;
1721 unsigned scc_entry_len;
1722 hashval_t scc_hash = lto_input_scc (&ib_main, data_in, &len_,
1723 &scc_entry_len);
1724 unsigned len = data_in->reader_cache->nodes.length () - from;
1725 gcc_assert (len == len_);
1726
1727 total_scc_size += len;
1728 num_sccs_read++;
1729
1730 /* We have the special case of size-1 SCCs that are pre-merged
1731 by means of identifier and string sharing for example.
1732 ??? Maybe we should avoid streaming those as SCCs. */
1733 tree first = streamer_tree_cache_get_tree (data_in->reader_cache,
1734 from);
1735 if (len == 1
1736 && (TREE_CODE (first) == IDENTIFIER_NODE
1737 || TREE_CODE (first) == INTEGER_CST
1738 || TREE_CODE (first) == TRANSLATION_UNIT_DECL))
1739 continue;
1740
1741 /* Try to unify the SCC with already existing ones. */
1742 if (!flag_ltrans
1743 && unify_scc (data_in, from,
1744 len, scc_entry_len, scc_hash))
1745 continue;
1746
1747 /* Tree merging failed, mark entries in location cache as
1748 permanent. */
1749 data_in->location_cache.accept_location_cache ();
1750
1751 bool seen_type = false;
1752 for (unsigned i = 0; i < len; ++i)
1753 {
1754 tree t = streamer_tree_cache_get_tree (data_in->reader_cache,
1755 from + i);
1756 /* Reconstruct the type variant and pointer-to/reference-to
1757 chains. */
1758 if (TYPE_P (t))
1759 {
1760 seen_type = true;
1761 num_prevailing_types++;
1762 lto_fixup_prevailing_type (t);
1763 }
1764 /* Compute the canonical type of all types.
1765 ??? Should be able to assert that !TYPE_CANONICAL. */
1766 if (TYPE_P (t) && !TYPE_CANONICAL (t))
1767 {
1768 gimple_register_canonical_type (t);
1769 if (odr_type_p (t))
1770 register_odr_type (t);
1771 }
1772 /* Link shared INTEGER_CSTs into TYPE_CACHED_VALUEs of its
1773 type which is also member of this SCC. */
1774 if (TREE_CODE (t) == INTEGER_CST
1775 && !TREE_OVERFLOW (t))
1776 cache_integer_cst (t);
1777 /* Register TYPE_DECLs with the debuginfo machinery. */
1778 if (!flag_wpa
1779 && TREE_CODE (t) == TYPE_DECL)
1780 {
1781 /* Dwarf2out needs location information.
1782 TODO: Moving this out of the streamer loop may noticealy
1783 improve ltrans linemap memory use. */
1784 data_in->location_cache.apply_location_cache ();
1785 debug_hooks->type_decl (t, !DECL_FILE_SCOPE_P (t));
1786 }
1787 if (!flag_ltrans)
1788 {
1789 lto_maybe_register_decl (data_in, t, from + i);
1790 /* Scan the tree for references to global functions or
1791 variables and record those for later fixup. */
1792 if (mentions_vars_p (t))
1793 vec_safe_push (tree_with_vars, t);
1794 }
1795 }
1796 if (seen_type)
1797 num_type_scc_trees += len;
1798 }
1799 else
1800 {
1801 /* Pickle stray references. */
1802 t = lto_input_tree_1 (&ib_main, data_in, tag, 0);
1803 gcc_assert (t && data_in->reader_cache->nodes.length () == from);
1804 }
1805 }
1806 data_in->location_cache.apply_location_cache ();
1807
1808 /* Read in lto_in_decl_state objects. */
1809 data_ptr = (const uint32_t *) ((const char*) data + decl_offset);
1810 data_end =
1811 (const uint32_t *) ((const char*) data_ptr + header->decl_state_size);
1812 num_decl_states = *data_ptr++;
1813
1814 gcc_assert (num_decl_states > 0);
1815 decl_data->global_decl_state = lto_new_in_decl_state ();
1816 data_ptr = lto_read_in_decl_state (data_in, data_ptr,
1817 decl_data->global_decl_state);
1818
1819 /* Read in per-function decl states and enter them in hash table. */
1820 decl_data->function_decl_states =
1821 hash_table<decl_state_hasher>::create_ggc (37);
1822
1823 for (i = 1; i < num_decl_states; i++)
1824 {
1825 struct lto_in_decl_state *state = lto_new_in_decl_state ();
1826
1827 data_ptr = lto_read_in_decl_state (data_in, data_ptr, state);
1828 lto_in_decl_state **slot
1829 = decl_data->function_decl_states->find_slot (state, INSERT);
1830 gcc_assert (*slot == NULL);
1831 *slot = state;
1832 }
1833
1834 if (data_ptr != data_end)
1835 internal_error ("bytecode stream: garbage at the end of symbols section");
1836
1837 /* Set the current decl state to be the global state. */
1838 decl_data->current_decl_state = decl_data->global_decl_state;
1839
1840 lto_data_in_delete (data_in);
1841}
1842
1843/* Custom version of strtoll, which is not portable. */
1844
1845static int64_t
1846lto_parse_hex (const char *p)
1847{
1848 int64_t ret = 0;
1849
1850 for (; *p != '\0'; ++p)
1851 {
1852 char c = *p;
1853 unsigned char part;
1854 ret <<= 4;
1855 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
1856 part = c - '0';
1857 else if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f')
1858 part = c - 'a' + 10;
1859 else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')
1860 part = c - 'A' + 10;
1861 else
1862 internal_error ("could not parse hex number");
1863 ret |= part;
1864 }
1865
1866 return ret;
1867}
1868
1869/* Read resolution for file named FILE_NAME. The resolution is read from
1870 RESOLUTION. */
1871
1872static void
1873lto_resolution_read (splay_tree file_ids, FILE *resolution, lto_file *file)
1874{
1875 /* We require that objects in the resolution file are in the same
1876 order as the lto1 command line. */
1877 unsigned int name_len;
1878 char *obj_name;
1879 unsigned int num_symbols;
1880 unsigned int i;
1881 struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data;
1882 splay_tree_node nd = NULL;
1883
1884 if (!resolution)
1885 return;
1886
1887 name_len = strlen (file->filename);
1888 obj_name = XNEWVEC (char, name_len + 1);
1889 fscanf (resolution, " "); /* Read white space. */
1890
1891 fread (obj_name, sizeof (char), name_len, resolution);
1892 obj_name[name_len] = '\0';
1893 if (filename_cmp (obj_name, file->filename) != 0)
1894 internal_error ("unexpected file name %s in linker resolution file. "
1895 "Expected %s", obj_name, file->filename);
1896 if (file->offset != 0)
1897 {
1898 int t;
1899 char offset_p[17];
1900 int64_t offset;
1901 t = fscanf (resolution, "@0x%16s", offset_p);
1902 if (t != 1)
1903 internal_error ("could not parse file offset");
1904 offset = lto_parse_hex (offset_p);
1905 if (offset != file->offset)
1906 internal_error ("unexpected offset");
1907 }
1908
1909 free (obj_name);
1910
1911 fscanf (resolution, "%u", &num_symbols);
1912
1913 for (i = 0; i < num_symbols; i++)
1914 {
1915 int t;
1916 unsigned index;
1917 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT id;
1918 char r_str[27];
1919 enum ld_plugin_symbol_resolution r = (enum ld_plugin_symbol_resolution) 0;
1920 unsigned int j;
1921 unsigned int lto_resolution_str_len =
1922 sizeof (lto_resolution_str) / sizeof (char *);
1923 res_pair rp;
1924
1925 t = fscanf (resolution, "%u " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_HEX_PURE " %26s %*[^\n]\n",
1926 &index, &id, r_str);
1927 if (t != 3)
1928 internal_error ("invalid line in the resolution file");
1929
1930 for (j = 0; j < lto_resolution_str_len; j++)
1931 {
1932 if (strcmp (lto_resolution_str[j], r_str) == 0)
1933 {
1934 r = (enum ld_plugin_symbol_resolution) j;
1935 break;
1936 }
1937 }
1938 if (j == lto_resolution_str_len)
1939 internal_error ("invalid resolution in the resolution file");
1940
1941 if (!(nd && lto_splay_tree_id_equal_p (nd->key, id)))
1942 {
1943 nd = lto_splay_tree_lookup (file_ids, id);
1944 if (nd == NULL)
1945 internal_error ("resolution sub id %wx not in object file", id);
1946 }
1947
1948 file_data = (struct lto_file_decl_data *)nd->value;
1949 /* The indexes are very sparse. To save memory save them in a compact
1950 format that is only unpacked later when the subfile is processed. */
1951 rp.res = r;
1952 rp.index = index;
1953 file_data->respairs.safe_push (rp);
1954 if (file_data->max_index < index)
1955 file_data->max_index = index;
1956 }
1957}

1959/* List of file_decl_datas */
1960struct file_data_list
1961 {
1962 struct lto_file_decl_data *first, *last;
1963 };

1965/* Is the name for a id'ed LTO section? */
1966
1967static int
1968lto_section_with_id (const char *name, unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT *id)
1969{
1970 const char *s;
1971
1972 if (strncmp (name, section_name_prefix, strlen (section_name_prefix)))
1973 return 0;
1974 s = strrchr (name, '.');
1975 return s && sscanf (s, "." HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_HEX_PURE, id) == 1;
1976}
1977
1978/* Create file_data of each sub file id */
1979
1980static int
1981create_subid_section_table (struct lto_section_slot *ls, splay_tree file_ids,
1982 struct file_data_list *list)
1983{
1984 struct lto_section_slot s_slot, *new_slot;
1985 unsigned HOST_WIDE_INT id;
1986 splay_tree_node nd;
1987 void **hash_slot;
1988 char *new_name;
1989 struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data;
1990
1991 if (!lto_section_with_id (ls->name, &id))
1992 return 1;
1993
1994 /* Find hash table of sub module id */
1995 nd = lto_splay_tree_lookup (file_ids, id);
1996 if (nd != NULL)
1997 {
1998 file_data = (struct lto_file_decl_data *)nd->value;
1999 }
2000 else
2001 {
2002 file_data = ggc_alloc<lto_file_decl_data> ();
2003 memset(file_data, 0, sizeof (struct lto_file_decl_data));
2004 file_data->id = id;
2005 file_data->section_hash_table = lto_obj_create_section_hash_table ();;
2006 lto_splay_tree_insert (file_ids, id, file_data);
2007
2008 /* Maintain list in linker order */
2009 if (!list->first)
2010 list->first = file_data;
2011 if (list->last)
2012 list->last->next = file_data;
2013 list->last = file_data;
2014 }
2015
2016 /* Copy section into sub module hash table */
2017 new_name = XDUPVEC (char, ls->name, strlen (ls->name) + 1);
2018 s_slot.name = new_name;
2019 hash_slot = htab_find_slot (file_data->section_hash_table, &s_slot, INSERT);
2020 gcc_assert (*hash_slot == NULL);
2021
2022 new_slot = XDUP (struct lto_section_slot, ls);
2023 new_slot->name = new_name;
2024 *hash_slot = new_slot;
2025 return 1;
2026}

2028/* Read declarations and other initializations for a FILE_DATA. */
2029
2030static void
2031lto_file_finalize (struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data, lto_file *file)
2032{
2033 const char *data;
2034 size_t len;
2035 vec<ld_plugin_symbol_resolution_t>
2036 resolutions = vNULL;
2037 int i;
2038 res_pair *rp;
2039
2040 /* Create vector for fast access of resolution. We do this lazily
2041 to save memory. */
2042 resolutions.safe_grow_cleared (file_data->max_index + 1);
2043 for (i = 0; file_data->respairs.iterate (i, &rp); i++)
2044 resolutions[rp->index] = rp->res;
2045 file_data->respairs.release ();
2046
2047 file_data->renaming_hash_table = lto_create_renaming_table ();
2048 file_data->file_name = file->filename;
2049#ifdef ACCEL_COMPILER
2050 lto_input_mode_table (file_data);
2051#else
2052 file_data->mode_table = lto_mode_identity_table;
2053#endif
2054 data = lto_get_section_data (file_data, LTO_section_decls, NULL, &len);
2055 if (data == NULL)
2056 {
2057 internal_error ("cannot read LTO decls from %s", file_data->file_name);
2058 return;
2059 }
2060 /* Frees resolutions */
2061 lto_read_decls (file_data, data, resolutions);
2062 lto_free_section_data (file_data, LTO_section_decls, NULL, data, len);
2063}

2065/* Finalize FILE_DATA in FILE and increase COUNT. */
2066
2067static int
2068lto_create_files_from_ids (lto_file *file, struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data,
2069 int *count)
2070{
2071 lto_file_finalize (file_data, file);
2072 if (symtab->dump_file)
2073 fprintf (symtab->dump_file,
2074 "Creating file %s with sub id " HOST_WIDE_INT_PRINT_HEX "\n",
2075 file_data->file_name, file_data->id);
2076 (*count)++;
2077 return 0;
2078}
2079
2080/* Generate a TREE representation for all types and external decls
2081 entities in FILE.
2082
2083 Read all of the globals out of the file. Then read the cgraph
2084 and process the .o index into the cgraph nodes so that it can open
2085 the .o file to load the functions and ipa information. */
2086
2087static struct lto_file_decl_data *
2088lto_file_read (lto_file *file, FILE *resolution_file, int *count)
2089{
2090 struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data = NULL;
2091 splay_tree file_ids;
2092 htab_t section_hash_table;
2093 struct lto_section_slot *section;
2094 struct file_data_list file_list;
2095 struct lto_section_list section_list;
2096
2097 memset (&section_list, 0, sizeof (struct lto_section_list));
2098 section_hash_table = lto_obj_build_section_table (file, &section_list);
2099
2100 /* Find all sub modules in the object and put their sections into new hash
2101 tables in a splay tree. */
2102 file_ids = lto_splay_tree_new ();
2103 memset (&file_list, 0, sizeof (struct file_data_list));
2104 for (section = section_list.first; section != NULL; section = section->next)
2105 create_subid_section_table (section, file_ids, &file_list);
2106
2107 /* Add resolutions to file ids */
2108 lto_resolution_read (file_ids, resolution_file, file);
2109
2110 /* Finalize each lto file for each submodule in the merged object */
2111 for (file_data = file_list.first; file_data != NULL; file_data = file_data->next)
2112 lto_create_files_from_ids (file, file_data, count);
2113
2114 splay_tree_delete (file_ids);
2115 htab_delete (section_hash_table);
2116
2117 return file_list.first;
2118}

2120#if HAVE_MMAP_FILE && HAVE_SYSCONF && defined _SC_PAGE_SIZE
2121#define LTO_MMAP_IO 1
2122#endif
2123
2124#if LTO_MMAP_IO
2125/* Page size of machine is used for mmap and munmap calls. */
2126static size_t page_mask;
2127#endif
2128
2129/* Get the section data of length LEN from FILENAME starting at
2130 OFFSET. The data segment must be freed by the caller when the
2131 caller is finished. Returns NULL if all was not well. */
2132
2133static char *
2134lto_read_section_data (struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data,
2135 intptr_t offset, size_t len)
2136{
2137 char *result;
2138 static int fd = -1;
2139 static char *fd_name;
2140#if LTO_MMAP_IO
2141 intptr_t computed_len;
2142 intptr_t computed_offset;
2143 intptr_t diff;
2144#endif
2145
2146 /* Keep a single-entry file-descriptor cache. The last file we
2147 touched will get closed at exit.
2148 ??? Eventually we want to add a more sophisticated larger cache
2149 or rather fix function body streaming to not stream them in
2150 practically random order. */
2151 if (fd != -1
2152 && filename_cmp (fd_name, file_data->file_name) != 0)
2153 {
2154 free (fd_name);
2155 close (fd);
2156 fd = -1;
2157 }
2158 if (fd == -1)
2159 {
2160 fd = open (file_data->file_name, O_RDONLY|O_BINARY);
2161 if (fd == -1)
2162 {
2163 fatal_error (input_location, "Cannot open %s", file_data->file_name);
2164 return NULL;
2165 }
2166 fd_name = xstrdup (file_data->file_name);
2167 }
2168
2169#if LTO_MMAP_IO
2170 if (!page_mask)
2171 {
2172 size_t page_size = sysconf (_SC_PAGE_SIZE);
2173 page_mask = ~(page_size - 1);
2174 }
2175
2176 computed_offset = offset & page_mask;
2177 diff = offset - computed_offset;
2178 computed_len = len + diff;
2179
2180 result = (char *) mmap (NULL, computed_len, PROT_READ, MAP_PRIVATE,
2181 fd, computed_offset);
2182 if (result == MAP_FAILED)
2183 {
2184 fatal_error (input_location, "Cannot map %s", file_data->file_name);
2185 return NULL;
2186 }
2187
2188 return result + diff;
2189#else
2190 result = (char *) xmalloc (len);
2191 if (lseek (fd, offset, SEEK_SET) != offset
2192 || read (fd, result, len) != (ssize_t) len)
2193 {
2194 free (result);
2195 fatal_error (input_location, "Cannot read %s", file_data->file_name);
2196 result = NULL;
2197 }
2198#ifdef __MINGW32__
2199 /* Native windows doesn't supports delayed unlink on opened file. So
2200 we close file here again. This produces higher I/O load, but at least
2201 it prevents to have dangling file handles preventing unlink. */
2202 free (fd_name);
2203 fd_name = NULL;
2204 close (fd);
2205 fd = -1;
2206#endif
2207 return result;
2208#endif
2209}

2212/* Get the section data from FILE_DATA of SECTION_TYPE with NAME.
2213 NAME will be NULL unless the section type is for a function
2214 body. */
2215
2216static const char *
2217get_section_data (struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data,
2218 enum lto_section_type section_type,
2219 const char *name,
2220 size_t *len)
2221{
2222 htab_t section_hash_table = file_data->section_hash_table;
2223 struct lto_section_slot *f_slot;
2224 struct lto_section_slot s_slot;
2225 const char *section_name = lto_get_section_name (section_type, name, file_data);
2226 char *data = NULL;
2227
2228 *len = 0;
2229 s_slot.name = section_name;
2230 f_slot = (struct lto_section_slot *) htab_find (section_hash_table, &s_slot);
2231 if (f_slot)
2232 {
2233 data = lto_read_section_data (file_data, f_slot->start, f_slot->len);
2234 *len = f_slot->len;
2235 }
2236
2237 free (CONST_CAST (char *, section_name));
2238 return data;
2239}

2242/* Free the section data from FILE_DATA of SECTION_TYPE with NAME that
2243 starts at OFFSET and has LEN bytes. */
2244
2245static void
2246free_section_data (struct lto_file_decl_data *file_data ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,
2247 enum lto_section_type section_type ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED,

2255#endif

2270/* Helper for qsort; compare partitions and return one with smaller size.
2271 We sort from greatest to smallest so parallel build doesn't stale on the
2272 longest compilation being executed too late. */
2273
2274static int
2275cmp_partitions_size (const void *a, const void *b)
2276{
2277 const struct ltrans_partition_def *pa
2278 = *(struct ltrans_partition_def *const *)a;
2279 const struct ltrans_partition_def *pb
2280 = *(struct ltrans_partition_def *const *)b;
2281 return pb->insns - pa->insns;
2282}
2283
2284/* Helper for qsort; compare partitions and return one with smaller order. */
2285
2286static int
2287cmp_partitions_order (const void *a, const void *b)
2288{
2289 const struct ltrans_partition_def *pa
2290 = *(struct ltrans_partition_def *const *)a;
2291 const struct ltrans_partition_def *pb
2292 = *(struct ltrans_partition_def *const *)b;
2293 int ordera = -1, orderb = -1;
2294
2295 if (lto_symtab_encoder_size (pa->encoder))
2296 ordera = lto_symtab_encoder_deref (pa->encoder, 0)->order;
2297 if (lto_symtab_encoder_size (pb->encoder))
2298 orderb = lto_symtab_encoder_deref (pb->encoder, 0)->order;
2299 return orderb - ordera;
2300}

2321/* Wait for forked process and signal errors. */
2322#ifdef HAVE_WORKING_FORK
2323static void
2324wait_for_child ()
2325{
2326 int status;
2327 do
2328 {
2329#ifndef WCONTINUED
2330#define WCONTINUED 0
2331#endif
2332 int w = waitpid (0, &status, WUNTRACED | WCONTINUED);
2333 if (w == -1)
2334 fatal_error (input_location, "waitpid failed");
2335
2336 if (WIFEXITED (status) && WEXITSTATUS (status))
2337 fatal_error (input_location, "streaming subprocess failed");
2338 else if (WIFSIGNALED (status))
2339 fatal_error (input_location,
2340 "streaming subprocess was killed by signal");
2341 }
2342 while (!WIFEXITED (status) && !WIFSIGNALED (status));
2343}
2344#endif
2345
2346/* Stream out ENCODER into TEMP_FILENAME
2347 Fork if that seems to help. */
2348
2349static void
2350stream_out (char *temp_filename, lto_symtab_encoder_t encoder,
2351 bool ARG_UNUSED (last))
2352{
2353#ifdef HAVE_WORKING_FORK
2354 static int nruns;
2355
2356 if (lto_parallelism <= 1)
2357 {
2358 do_stream_out (temp_filename, encoder);
2359 return;
2360 }
2361
2362 /* Do not run more than LTO_PARALLELISM streamings
2363 FIXME: we ignore limits on jobserver. */
2364 if (lto_parallelism > 0 && nruns >= lto_parallelism)
2365 {
2366 wait_for_child ();
2367 nruns --;
2368 }
2369 /* If this is not the last parallel partition, execute new
2370 streaming process. */
2371 if (!last)
2372 {
2373 pid_t cpid = fork ();
2374
2375 if (!cpid)
2376 {
2377 setproctitle ("lto1-wpa-streaming");
2378 do_stream_out (temp_filename, encoder);
2379 exit (0);
2380 }
2381 /* Fork failed; lets do the job ourseleves. */
2382 else if (cpid == -1)
2383 do_stream_out (temp_filename, encoder);
2384 else
2385 nruns++;
2386 }
2387 /* Last partition; stream it and wait for all children to die. */
2388 else
2389 {
2390 int i;
2391 do_stream_out (temp_filename, encoder);
2392 for (i = 0; i < nruns; i++)
2393 wait_for_child ();
2394 }
2395 asm_nodes_output = true;
2396#else
2397 do_stream_out (temp_filename, encoder);
2398#endif
2399}

2401/* Write all output files in WPA mode and the file with the list of
2402 LTRANS units. */
2403
2404static void
2405lto_wpa_write_files (void)
2406{
2407 unsigned i, n_sets;
2408 ltrans_partition part;
2409 FILE *ltrans_output_list_stream;
2410 char *temp_filename;
2411 vec <char *>temp_filenames = vNULL;
2412 size_t blen;
2413
2414 /* Open the LTRANS output list. */
2415 if (!ltrans_output_list)
2416 fatal_error (input_location, "no LTRANS output list filename provided");
2417
2418 timevar_push (TV_WHOPR_WPA);
2419
2420 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (ltrans_partitions, i, part)
2421 lto_stats.num_output_symtab_nodes += lto_symtab_encoder_size (part->encoder);
2422
2423 timevar_pop (TV_WHOPR_WPA);
2424
2425 timevar_push (TV_WHOPR_WPA_IO);
2426
2427 /* Generate a prefix for the LTRANS unit files. */
2428 blen = strlen (ltrans_output_list);
2429 temp_filename = (char *) xmalloc (blen + sizeof ("2147483648.o"));
2430 strcpy (temp_filename, ltrans_output_list);
2431 if (blen > sizeof (".out")
2432 && strcmp (temp_filename + blen - sizeof (".out") + 1,
2433 ".out") == 0)
2434 temp_filename[blen - sizeof (".out") + 1] = '\0';
2435 blen = strlen (temp_filename);
2436
2437 n_sets = ltrans_partitions.length ();
2438
2439 /* Sort partitions by size so small ones are compiled last.
2440 FIXME: Even when not reordering we may want to output one list for parallel make
2441 and other for final link command. */
2442
2443 if (!flag_profile_reorder_functions || !flag_profile_use)
2444 ltrans_partitions.qsort (flag_toplevel_reorder
2445 ? cmp_partitions_size
2446 : cmp_partitions_order);
2447
2448 for (i = 0; i < n_sets; i++)
2449 {
2450 ltrans_partition part = ltrans_partitions[i];
2451
2452 /* Write all the nodes in SET. */
2453 sprintf (temp_filename + blen, "%u.o", i);
2454
2455 if (!quiet_flag)
2456 fprintf (stderr, " %s (%s %i insns)", temp_filename, part->name, part->insns);
2457 if (symtab->dump_file)
2458 {
2459 lto_symtab_encoder_iterator lsei;
2460
2461 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "Writing partition %s to file %s, %i insns\n",
2462 part->name, temp_filename, part->insns);
2463 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, " Symbols in partition: ");
2464 for (lsei = lsei_start_in_partition (part->encoder); !lsei_end_p (lsei);
2465 lsei_next_in_partition (&lsei))
2466 {
2467 symtab_node *node = lsei_node (lsei);
2468 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "%s ", node->asm_name ());
2469 }
2470 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "\n Symbols in boundary: ");
2471 for (lsei = lsei_start (part->encoder); !lsei_end_p (lsei);
2472 lsei_next (&lsei))
2473 {
2474 symtab_node *node = lsei_node (lsei);
2475 if (!lto_symtab_encoder_in_partition_p (part->encoder, node))
2476 {
2477 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "%s ", node->asm_name ());
2478 cgraph_node *cnode = dyn_cast <cgraph_node *> (node);
2479 if (cnode
2480 && lto_symtab_encoder_encode_body_p (part->encoder, cnode))
2481 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "(body included)");
2482 else
2483 {
2484 varpool_node *vnode = dyn_cast <varpool_node *> (node);
2485 if (vnode
2486 && lto_symtab_encoder_encode_initializer_p (part->encoder, vnode))
2487 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "(initializer included)");
2488 }
2489 }
2490 }
2491 fprintf (symtab->dump_file, "\n");
2492 }
2493 gcc_checking_assert (lto_symtab_encoder_size (part->encoder) || !i);
2494
2495 stream_out (temp_filename, part->encoder, i == n_sets - 1);
2496
2497 part->encoder = NULL;
2498
2499 temp_filenames.safe_push (xstrdup (temp_filename));
2500 }
2501 ltrans_output_list_stream = fopen (ltrans_output_list, "w");
2502 if (ltrans_output_list_stream == NULL)
2503 fatal_error (input_location,
2504 "opening LTRANS output list %s: %m", ltrans_output_list);
2505 for (i = 0; i < n_sets; i++)
2506 {
2507 unsigned int len = strlen (temp_filenames[i]);
2508 if (fwrite (temp_filenames[i], 1, len, ltrans_output_list_stream) < len
2509 || fwrite ("\n", 1, 1, ltrans_output_list_stream) < 1)
2510 fatal_error (input_location, "writing to LTRANS output list %s: %m",
2511 ltrans_output_list);
2512 free (temp_filenames[i]);
2513 }
2514 temp_filenames.release();
2515
2516 lto_stats.num_output_files += n_sets;
2517
2518 /* Close the LTRANS output list. */
2519 if (fclose (ltrans_output_list_stream))
2520 fatal_error (input_location,
2521 "closing LTRANS output list %s: %m", ltrans_output_list);
2522
2523 free_ltrans_partitions();
2524 free (temp_filename);
2525
2526 timevar_pop (TV_WHOPR_WPA_IO);
2527}
